                              <p style="font-size: 19px; color: black; font-style: italic;">“Do the thing you fear to do and keep on doing it…that is the quickest and surest way ever yet discovered to conquer fear.”
                                <p style="font-size: 19px; color: black; font-style: italic;">~Dale Carnegie</p> 
                              <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                The exam season often brings a huge load of uncomfortable feelings with it. As exams approach us, we usually start overthinking and feel anxious. Our stress levels increase, sleep patterns get disrupted, and we feel restless and nervous. Most of us encounter these feelings, and it is okay to feel a little nervous before exams. However, when our stress levels increase exponentially, it interferes with our functioning and well-being. This is where exam fear becomes detrimental. It is imperative to confront and overcome extreme exam fear. These are a few tips that you can implement to feel confident before giving your exams. 

                                </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';"><li>●	Exclude Distractions  </li>
                                  <li>●	Be Consistent with Your Studies  </li>
                                  <li>●	Avoid Last-Minute Preparation </li>
                                  <li>●	Revise Beforehand  </li>
                                  <li>●	Watch YouTube Videos </li>
                                  <li>●	Take Peer Support</li>
                                  <li>●	Express Your Feelings </li>
                                  <li>●	Focus on Input Instead of Output </li>
                                  <li>●	Don’t Burden Yourself with Expectations </li>
                                  <li>●	Choose Personal Satisfaction Over Unhealthy Competition</li>
                                  <li>●	Take Mock/Practice Tests </li>
                                  <li>●	Take Care of Your Health</li>
                                  <li>●	Look at the Larger Picture</li>
                                  <li>●	Don’t Associate Your Self-Worth with Academic Validation </li>
                                   
                                  	</ul> 
                                  
                              </p>
                               
